cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem related to graph theory and memory devices, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of the Lovasz local lemma and the analysis of the asymptotic behavior of the writing capacity suggest that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on finding a valid coloring with the largest number of colors for a subgraph of a given directed graph suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of probabilistic methods and the analysis of the asymptotic expression suggest that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
